# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# tomcedoz.com — what NOT to publish.
# This is a plain static HTML/CSS site. After `git init`, `git add .` will
# stage everything EXCEPT the files matched below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Private / source materials — never publish
# Original full-res headshot. Optimized copy is in assets/tom-cedoz.jpg.
HH_60799955_Tom_Cedoz.jpg
# Source manuscripts, including other authors' unpublished work.
Writing/
# Internal content-audit notes; working files, not for the public.
review/
# Internal QA backlog; do not publish.
WEBSITE_BACKLOG.md
# Internal legal/brand/privacy/browser review packet; do not publish.
LAUNCH_REVIEW_PACKET.md
# Generated deploy allowlist output.
dist/
# Internal advertising/dissemination snapshots; retain, do not publish.
ad-records/

# Logo marks made for the MUEFS project — not used by this website
logo/

# Local tooling / caches / editor / OS cruft
# Local Claude Code + preview-server config.
.claude/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.playwright-mcp/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log

# Scratch / preview pages (in case any get regenerated)
*-preview.html
*-options.html

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Build tooling + content source + internal config — LOCAL ONLY.
# Porkbun serves the repo root AS the live site, so the public repo holds
# ONLY the deployable website. These build/dev files stay on this machine and
# are never pushed (their output is already baked into the committed HTML).
# NOTE: GitHub no longer backs these up — keep another copy somewhere safe.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.py
resources/_data/
seo/
content_review.json
privacy_inventory.json
site_policy.json
